==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[būr]]'', "dwelling" < Indo-European, "be, live"

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A large nest made of grass and bright objects, used by the [[bower bird]] during [[courtship]] displays.
# Shady shelter: a shady leafy shelter or recess in a garden or woods
# Woman's bedroom or apartments: a woman's bedroom or private apartments, especially in a medieval castle
# Picturesque cottage: a picturesque country cottage, especially one that is used as a retreat ( literary ) 
# (Nautical) A bower is a type of ship's anchor; so named from being carried at the bow of a ship.

